---
// /get — download the native Windows client.
//
// The client ships as a SELF-CONTAINED Windows installer (no .NET runtime required), published as a
// GitHub Release asset by .github/workflows/release-windows.yml. The download link points at the
// repo's "latest release" with a STABLE asset name, so it always resolves to the newest installer
// without editing this page per version. (Anonymous download requires the repo to be public.)
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';

const DOWNLOAD_URL =
  'https://github.com/snowboardcto/markdown-web/releases/latest/download/TheMarkdownWeb-Setup.exe';
const RELEASES_URL = 'https://github.com/snowboardcto/markdown-web/releases/latest';
---

<Page title="Get the Markdown Web client">
  <h1>Get the Markdown Web client</h1>

  <p>
    The native client is a <strong>browser for the Markdown Web</strong>: type a
    <code>.md</code> URL and your machine renders it as a clean, native document —
    no embedded web browser, no HTML. Today it ships the <em>faithful basic</em>
    render; AI personalities come next.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="download" href={DOWNLOAD_URL} rel="nofollow">⬇ Download for Windows</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Install</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Run <code>TheMarkdownWeb-Setup.exe</code>.</li>
    <li>It's <strong>self-contained</strong> — nothing else to install (no .NET runtime needed).</li>
    <li>
      The installer isn't code-signed yet, so Windows SmartScreen may say
      “unknown publisher.” Choose <strong>More info → Run anyway</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Launch <strong>The Markdown Web</strong>, then open a page — e.g. paste a
      <code>themarkdownweb.com/&hellip;.md</code> URL into the address bar.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p class="muted">
    Windows 10/11 (x64). Trouble with the button? Grab it from the
    <a href={RELEASES_URL} rel="nofollow">latest release</a>.
    macOS and Linux clients are on the roadmap.
  </p>

  <p><a href="/">← Back to the web</a></p>
</Page>

<style>
  .download {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: #1f2328;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .download:hover { background: #0d1117; }
  .muted { color: #59636e; font-size: 0.925rem; }
</style>
